cs.SD, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.SI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with the problem of voice activity detection using artificial neural networks and features derived from the power spectral density and periodicity of the signal. This falls under the sub-category of Signal Processing (cs.SD) and Natural Language Processing (cs.CL). The use of artificial neural networks for classification also suggests the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE). Finally, the mutual information-based assessment of the features suggests the sub-category of Information Theory (cs.IT) as well, but this is less likely than the others.
